The recipe did not change in the version migration, a URL did not hash, or there is jinja2 syntax the bot cannot handle!

Please check the URLs in your recipe with version '0.8.1' to make sure they exist!

We also found the following errors:

 - could not hash URL template 'https://github.com/pypr/compyle/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz'

raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "compyle" %}
{% set version = "0.5" %}

package:
  name: "{{ name|lower }}"
  version: "{{ version }}"

source:
  url: https://github.com/pypr/compyle/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: eb8594d9116505ff4ad5111bef3f500a7ad22771a588e6d176048d2e9da355af

build:
  number: 4
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps --ignore-installed -vv "
  
requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - cython
  host:
    - cython
    - mako
    - mock >=1.0
    - numpy
    - python
    - setuptools
    - pytools
    - pip
  run:
    - mako
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}
    - python
    - pytools
    
test:
  imports:
    - compyle
  
about:
  home: https://github.com/pypr/compyle
  license: BSD-3-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE.txt
  summary: Execute a subset of Python on HPC platforms
  doc_url: https://compyle.readthedocs.io/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - rishi9699
